By ellocopato<br>
<br>
The First Floor:<br>
----------------<br>
<br>
Upon entering the tower the first things that you will notice is a huge hole in the floor and many doors. <br>
<br>
Directly infront of you will be a door with two banners hanging from the sides.<br>
Specters called “Lesser Ice Shades” spawn on either side of the door. They have a very slow respawn rate however, remember this door for later reference.<br>
<br>
Traps Warning: <br>
Careful the floor is very slippery and inside the hole are 3 shadowbone skeletons that think you very tasty.<br>
<br>
<br>
Proceed to the second left-hand door, inside this room are many shadowbone skeletons, kill them then camp the hallway of this room. Pull as you like from the other rooms. <br>
<br>
Eventually one of two things will happen: <br>
(1 The Rare will spawn in one of the rooms <br>
(2 The Keyholder will instaspawn once what you’re killing is dead. <br>
<br>
The Keyholder is “A Large Undead Gnoll” and drops the Crystal Key, the key to then next level.<br>
<br>
The Rare is “Xalgoti” a named Shadowbeast, he drops Crystallized Shadow Tunic rarely.<br>
<br>
Grab the key and proceed to the double bannared door previously mentioned. On the left-hand side is a port to the 7th level but needs a key from the boss mob of the tower so skip it for now, and head to the right-hand side. Put the key on your mouse cursor and make sure your entire group is close to you, and hit U (Note for multiple raid groups you’ll need a key for each group it only takes up the groupmembers of the keyholders’ group).<br>
<br>
The Mirror Out:<br>
The mirror out on this floor is right behind of port in.<br>
<br>
The Drops on this level:<br>
Various Gnome Skin Armor (Crappy AC with Poison resist looks like pure black cloth with no designs.)<br>
Various Fading Shadow Weapons<br>
Shadow Bone Earrings (4 Agi 2 Int)<br>
And Various Crystallized Armor (Low ac high stats)<br>
A Crystal Key<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The Second floor:<br>
-----------------<br>
<br>
Upon port up you will enter an old library filled with Erudite Ghosts. Buff up MR immediately and switch on Resist gear, because nearly everything on this floor casts.<br>
<br>
<br>
Trap Warning:<br>
There is a bookshelf on the right-hand side of the Port Up that screams like a cougar and will claw you. Rogues can disarm this. It will not follow you, so more of a little flavor trap.<br>
<br>
Now you can either sit at port in and pull to there or wander around killing the erudite ghosts. There are way too much spawn on this level to point out but they’re nearly all Necromancers, Magicians, Wizards, or Enchanters. <br>
<br>
There are a few static spawns I should point out, on the booth infront of port in are the Librarian and The Librarian Assistant, these both don’t drop anything special other then crystallized but are named. The second is a hut left of the Port up, inside is a Ghostly Teacher and a Student, both drop nothing.<br>
<br>
Kill the ghosts and eventually one of two things will happen:<br>
(1 the keyholder will instaspawn once your target is dead<br>
(2 The Rare will spawn.<br>
<br>
The Keyholder is “A Angry Librarian” and drops the following<br>
<br>
Angry Librarian:<br>
<br>
The Three Toothed Key (Always)<br>
<br>
Students Homework (Uncommon)<br>
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM <br>
+3 INT, +15 MANA, +10 MR<br>
WT: 1.0<br>
Class: NEC, WIZ, MAG, ENC<br>
Race: HUM, ERU, HIE, DEF, HEF, GNM, IKS<br>
<br>
