The Fourth Floor:<br>
-----------------<br>
<br>
As you port in you will notice you are in a brick maze, it’s mostly like a crypt. Buff your MR and Disease Resistance because The Shadows on this cast nasty spells, and the Ancient Mummies Proc Disease. Make sure to switch on your Resist gear! Be prepared to fight because there are many wanderers<br>
<br>
<br>
Trap Warning: If you go the wrong way there are fake floors that drop you into a room with a few mobs, run into the fire in the center and you will be teleported to the port up area.<br>
<br>
Early Mirror Out:<br>
From the port in on your right is a White door, you can open this with either the key from the previous level or Lockpicks. **not sure skill worked for me at 200 lol** behind it are 3 mobs, kill them or run by them and there is a Mirror at the end of the tunnel, click on it and you will zone out.<br>
<br>
<br>
This maze is tricky, I offer you both a map link and directions<br>
<br>
Link: www.eqmaps.com/mapz/tower_level4.jpg<br>
<br>
Directions: <br>
Ignore the white door and take the first right you see, follow this tunnel but ignore the right turn you’ll see, this is a dead end with a mummy. Continue straight and ignore the left turn into a fake wall. Continue straight and you will come upon a single shadow, kill it and make sure you have a lot of mana and health. Next move up or pull the 4 Shadows and fight them. <br>
<br>
When rested head straight through the fake wall where the shadows hung out. There is sometimes a wanderer in this hall, kill it head straight and enter the mummy room. Cara Omica could be spawned in the empty coffin so be prepared. There is also a mummy that spawns in here if I remember correctly. This is your camp area. Sit down and pull the other rooms to you. Infront of you is the mirror to the 5th level, and 4 shadowmen in sets of 2.<br>
<br>
