Upon entering this level you will find many of the same creatures that were on level 1 except a lot harder. Ice shades and Shadow Beasts walk these halls as well as spirits of the undead.<br>
<br>
<br>
Trap Warning: Dragon statue AoE: stay away from the Dragon statue in the room with the ice shades and the mirror out. To know it’s the dangerous one check its hands, if they are flaming and smoking STAY AWAY!!<br>
<br>
Rare Info on this level: <br>
Killing stuff on this level might result in the spawn of<br>
An Incoherent Spirit. Kill him and randomly a Coherent Spirit will spawn. He's for a Kael Drakkal quest, nice reward. He can be found if you go all the way straight from the zonein (to the wall/banner), then turn right and right again.<br>
<br>
A incoherent spirit spawns on level 6 at the aforementioned place, has a rare drop "Abram's Axe of the Stoic", really nice melee weapon. Rare instaspawn off of incoherent's death is an npc quest ghost "lucid spirit of Abram". Part of a long and involved quest from Kael/Wakening. Lucid initially cons indiff to any faction when first spawned but will aggro when attacked and/or if you are fighting a mob near it.<br>
<br>
Proceed to forward killing anything that gets in your way and you come into a hallway with many turns and directions to take. Head right killing anything in your way, or camp here and pull the right till clear. <br>
<br>
Once the beasts are dead proceed up the stairs until you get to a platform above a library. Stay close, don’t fall off or get close to the edge or you will argo the Ice shades below. There are 3 beasts<br>
In the door to the platform, kill them and then rest up. When you are ready have each person on the raid click the mirror (no keys are needed)<br>
<br>
The Mirror Out:<br>
<br>
The Mirror Out on this level is hard to explain, but from port in head straight ignoring the first left, then take a second left. This should hopefully lead you to a room full of ice shades. Invis or pull them and kill. <br>
<br>
Avoid the Dragon Statue AT ALL COSTS stay away from it, it casts a nasty AoE that dropped our fully cleric buffed 53 warrior 2 bubs in seconds. If you are invis, hug the left wall all the way around till you get to the hallway out. Follow the hallway and click on the mirror to be transported out of this hellish room.<br>
<br>
<br>
