<br>
AOEs. Scary eh but you be amazed how effective AOEs are in here. Standard group I am usually with is a 54 druid, 50 wizard, 53 cleric and 2-4 variety of classes (I am 55 Shaman). We actually move rapidly thru the tower from 1 - 4 in record time (have keys, do not waste time slaughtering all before us, blah blah blah..heh). The bottleneck we found to 5th floor where the fun is (btw recommend 4th floor for excellent hunting from mid 30's to mid 40's) is on the 4th floor at the point where you come across 4-6 mobs all together. Pretty hard to single pull them and they tend to have a high agro radius. Usually we just tried to fight thru them with group taking damage from them and having major downtime after fight. Now here I give credit to Brairwolf, the 54 Druid, for coming up with AOEs. Basically he used Upheavel along with the cleric. The wizard would toss her point blank AOE after too to mop up. My god it was gross. The usual long fight was over in 1 min. Next place we found AOEs great for was the wedding. The wedding party per se (not bride/groom) do not agro you. You can move up to them w/o a care. Again here have 2-3 people crank AOEs and you can take down most if not all 8 zombie mobs there. Frankly AOEs are effective in the tower and I do recommend you use them. Just make sure 2 people are doing AOES so agro is not all built up on one person.<br>
